tity, and a description of the action performed.\n5.2 Immutability: Audit trails must be secured against modifications, edits, or deletion by any user, including system administrators and database developers. The system architecture must preclude any facility to pause, disable, or rewrite logged metadata.\n5.3 Regular Review: System audit trails must be reviewed by the Quality Assurance (QA) Department at least once every 30 calendar days. The review must be exhaustive, and evidence of review shall be documented via a cryptographically signed electronic audit attestation log.\n5.4 Retention: Audit trails must be retained for a duration no less than the retention requirements of the electronic records they document, and in a format that ensures readability and integrity throughout the retention period.\n\n6.0 DUAL-AUTHORIZATION FOR SOP MODIFICATIONS AND DOCUMENT RELEASES\nAny modification to this SOP or any other GxP document, as well as the release of such documents, shall require electronic approval by at least two authorized individuals. The system must enforce a dual-signature workflow, capturing the date, time, and identity of each approver in the audit trail.\n\n7.0 COMPLIANCE\nFailure to adhere to this SOP may result in regulatory non-compliance and disciplinary action. All personnel are responsible for reporting any suspected violations or system anomalies to QA immediately.\n\nORIGINAL SOP TEXT:\n\nSTANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE: SOP-103\nTITLE: SYSTEM AUDIT TRAILS AND DATA INTEGRITY\nVERSION: 1\n\n1.0 PURPOSE\nDefines the management, protection, and review of system audit trails to prevent unauthorized modifications and ensure record traceability.\n\n2.0 SCOPE\nApplies to all computer-generated, time-stamped audit trails recording the date, time, user identity, and specific actions of system transactions.\n\n3.0 AUDIT TRAIL MANAGEMENT\n3.1 Automatic Generation: Audit trails must be automatically generated by the system and capture all record creation, modification, and deletion events.\n3.2 Immutability: Audit trails must be secured against modifications, edits, or deletion by any user, including system administrators and database developers.\n3.3 Regular Review: System audit trails must be reviewed by the Quality Assurance (QA) Department at least once every 30 days. Evidence of audit trail review must be documented.\n3.4 Retention: Audit trails must be retained for a duration no less than the retention requirements of the electronic records they document.\n\n\nPlease analyze the additions/deletions and outline the operational tasks required to execute this update."
